cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.CL

This paper is about embedding large information networks into low-dimensional vector spaces, which is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. Based on the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper specifically mentions social networks and citation networks as examples of real-world information networks that were used in the experiments. The second most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a novel network embedding method that optimizes an objective function and uses an edge-sampling algorithm to improve inference. The third most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper mentions that the embedding method is useful for tasks such as node classification and link prediction. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes a new algorithm for embedding large information networks that addresses the limitations of existing methods. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper mentions language networks as another example of real-world information networks that were used in the experiments.
